In [6]:
# Displaying one random image of each plant

fi,ax = plt.subplots(4,3,figsize=(20,30))
row = 0
col = 0
index = 0
for i in lst:
    file_list = listdir(path+'\\'+i)
    file_name = random.sample(file_list, 1)[0]
    img = io.imread(path+'\\'+i+'\\'+file_name)
    ax[row][col].imshow(img, interpolation='nearest')
    ax[row][col].title.set_text(str(i)+' : '+str(file_name))
    index = index + 10
    col = col + 1
    if col > 2:
        row = row + 1
        col = 0
plt.show()

Forming the Training Dataset.¶

Imageset = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1/255)

Imageset_Dataset = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    validation_split=0.2) # set validation split

TrainingSet_SL = Imageset_Dataset.flow_from_directory(
    r'C:\Users\ramad\Desktop\Great Learning (AI_ML)\Module 9 - Computer Vision\Project 1\Part-1 - Plant Seedling Classification Data\train',
    target_size=(64, 64),
    batch_size=3816,
    class_mode='categorical',
    subset='training') # set as training data

ValidationSet_SL = Imageset_Dataset.flow_from_directory(
    r'C:\Users\ramad\Desktop\Great Learning (AI_ML)\Module 9 - Computer Vision\Project 1\Part-1 - Plant Seedling Classification Data\train', # same directory as training data
    target_size=(64, 64),
    batch_size=951,
    shuffle=False,
    class_mode='categorical',
    subset='validation') # set as validation data

Creating a Logistic Classification Model¶
In [14]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression

LogTrain = Logmod.score(X_train, Ys_train)
LogTest = Logmod.score(X_test, Ys_test)

            'C' : uniform(0.001,100),

Neural networks¶

Creating a Fully Connected or Dense Layer Model¶
In [37]:
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, LeakyReLU, PReLU, BatchNormalization, Conv2D, MaxPool2D, Flatten
from tensorflow.keras import regularizers, optimizers
In [38]:
def DenModLK(iterations, lr, lam, batch):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential()
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(2048))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.25))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(1024))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.25))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(512))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.25))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(256))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.25))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(12, activation='softmax', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(lam)))
    
    adam = optimizers.Adam(lr=lr, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=1e-07, decay=1e-6, amsgrad=False)
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    model.fit(TrainingSet_NN, epochs=iterations, batch_size=batch, verbose=1, validation_data=ValidationSet_NN)
    global DM
    DM = model

def DenMod(iterations, lr, lam, batch):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential()
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(4096, activation='relu'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(2048, activation='relu'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(1024, activation='relu'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(12, activation='softmax', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(lam)))
    
    adam = optimizers.Adam(lr=lr, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=1e-07, decay=1e-6, amsgrad=False)
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    model.fit(TrainingSet_NN, epochs=iterations, batch_size=batch, verbose=1, validation_data=ValidationSet_NN)
    global Densemod
    Densemod = model

Creating a Convolutional Model¶
In [43]:
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, LeakyReLU, PReLU, BatchNormalization, Conv2D, MaxPool2D, Flatten
from tensorflow.keras import regularizers, optimizers
In [44]:
def ModCl(iterations, lr, lam, batch):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential()
    model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(64,64,3), padding='same'))
    model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))
    model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', padding='same'))
    model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))
    model.add(Conv2D(64, (3,3), activation='relu', padding='same'))
    model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))
    model.add(Conv2D(128, (3,3), activation='relu', padding='same'))
    model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(1024, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(12, activation='softmax', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(lam)))
    
    adam = optimizers.Adam(lr=lr, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=1e-07, decay=1e-6, amsgrad=False)
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    model.fit(TrainingSet_NN, epochs=iterations, batch_size=batch, verbose=1, validation_data=ValidationSet_NN)
    global CNN1
    CNN1 = model

                        columns=[f"Predicted {i}" for i in ValidationSet_NN.class_indices.keys()])
